spec/code-quality-tracker.md:146:**Blast radius:** Medium. Every selector callsite stays valid if we keep the public hook surface; internal store wiring changes.
spec/code-quality-tracker.md:148:**Problem.** A single `create()` call holds: hydration state, snapshot/elements, violations, viewer/orbit/visibility, plan tools, collaboration, activity, and category overrides. Hot-reload thrashes the whole tree on any mutation. The store is hard to test in isolation. Derived inline imports (`import('./storeTypes').CategoryOverrides`) suggest the file is fighting circular-dep gravity.
spec/code-quality-tracker.md:152:- Store sliced into ≥3 stores by concern. Suggested:
spec/code-quality-tracker.md:157:- Public selector API for the rest of the app stays stable: `useBimStore(selector)` continues to work, either as a façade that pulls from the slices or by migrating callsites incrementally.
spec/code-quality-tracker.md:158:- No store imports another via dynamic `import()`.
spec/code-quality-tracker.md:159:- Existing tests pass; add at least one new unit test per new store covering the basic mutations.
spec/code-quality-tracker.md:161:**Approach note.** Easiest path: introduce slices using the [zustand "slices" pattern](https://docs.pmnd.rs/zustand/guides/slices-pattern) inside the existing `useBimStore` first (zero callsite churn). Then, in a follow-up PR, extract slices that are genuinely independent (most likely `useCollabStore`) into their own store.
